Then, I will use this user ID to filter posts in the 'posts' table, specifically looking for the 'Title' column. Since the hint specifies using the DisplayName for the user lookup, I will join the 'users' table to the 'posts' table on the 'OwnerUserId'. Therefore, I'll first select the user ID from the 'users' table and then match it with the posts to get the title of each post that this user has authored. I will ensure to select only the necessary columns based on the question requirements.
SQL: SELECT T1.Title FROM posts T1 JOIN users T2 ON T1.OwnerUserId = T2.Id WHERE T2.DisplayName = 'csgillespie'
